<P>
   SPYING-WORKPLACE (Undated) _ X. works for a large
telecommunications-equipment maker gathering intelligence about its
competitors. At trade shows, he tries to wheedle information from
rival companies' employees without letting them know who he is. He
agreed to be interviewed on condition that neither he nor his
employer be identified.
</P>
<P>
   OFFICE-KITCHEN (Undated) _ At many fast companies, and even some
