computer bug, and not a publicity stunt.
</P>
<P>
   The 360-foot-long sub, with a crew of 130, used sophisticated
satellite positioning technology to determine the proper location.
Up above, boats of various sizes circled the area.
</P>
<P>
   Q: An article Dec. 31 reported that Sarah Knauss, the world's
oldest living person, had died at 119. Who is now the oldest living
person, and what is the age?
</P>
<P>
   A: Researchers at Guinness Book of World Records are trying to
