<P>
   SCIENCE/MEDICINE
</P>
<P>
   ASTRONOMY-FUSE _ ATLANTA _ The first scientific findings from
NASA's Far Ultraviolet Spectroscopic Explorer, or ``FUSE,''
satellite are to be presented Wednesday at the American
Astronomical Society meeting in Atlanta. The orbiting telescope is
exploring the universe in light wavelengths that are blocked by the
earth's atmosphere and invisible to the Hubble Space Telescope.
Scientists from Johns Hopkins University, the University of
Wisconsin-Madison and the University of Colorado-Boulder will
describe what it has been seeing. (Nesmith, Cox News Service)
</P>
<P>
   (Moving in (a) National category.)
</P>
<P>
   ASTRONOMY-SPACELIFE _ ATLANTA _ Two groups, including one made
up of recognized experts from several countries, Wednesday will
describe calculations which they say suggest that astronomical
processes could have contributed to the appearance of life on
Earth. (Nesmith, Cox News Service)
</P>
<P>
   (Moving in (a) National category.)
</P>
