   FOOD-SKUBE-BEERCOLUMN _ Michael Skube's beer column is not
available this week.
</P>
<P>
   FOOD-CYBERSPICE _ A weekly column looking at the plethora of
recipes on the Internet. (Parham, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   FOOD-HASH _ If you think you're too time-pressed to fix dinner,
consider your grandmother, who didn't have a microwave or
dishwasher or a cupboard full of convenience foods at her
fingertips. And she had some pretty good ideas about how to do it
as efficiently as possible. Sometimes she made a hash of it.
Literally. It's too bad that today's cooks have forgotten about the
simple supper called hash. (Dayton Daily News). 35. WITH RECIPES
and an ILLUSTRATION. MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   WINE-COLUMN _ I was able to take some time off from work over
the holidays, and during that period, I tasted and slurped up some
wonderful, awesome, just real fine wines. Some were mine, but the
best fermented juice to cross my tongue belonged to friends
generous enough to share wines for which they paid, quite frankly,
a pretty penny. Tasting them reminded me of a question I've heard
repeatedly posed to wine sellers and tasters about expensive wines:
``Are they worth that much more? Is a $50 wine really 10 times
better than a $5 bottle?'' The answer is: No, of course not. And,
the answer is: Well, maybe. (Fisher, Dayton Daily News). 15. MOVED.
</P>
