   ENTERTAINMENT (``e'' category)
</P>
<P>
   FLEDGLING-FILMMAKER (San Francisco) _ Filmmakers in search of a
producer and production companies on the lookout for filmmakers
will meet Thursday through Sunday at the International Film
Financing Conference in San Francisco. By DAVID ARMSTRONG.
</P>
<P>
   FILM-REVIEW-FRIDAY (Undated) _ Calling all fans of excrement:
Your time has come. Run, don't walk, to the nearest neighborhood
screening of ``Next Friday,'' where you can soak in scatology to
your heart's (or whatever's) content. That the film tempers plop
jokes with racist stereotypes and near-constant ``Cheech &AMP;
Chong''-esque marijuana consumption will make it either more or
less palatable to the individual viewer. You decide. By AMY
BIANCOLLI.
</P>
<P>
   FOOD (`d'' category)
</P>
<P>
   FOOD-GREENS (Undated) _ Greens give people the blues. Leafy
green vegetables are known for being hard to clean, stinky to cook
and bitter to taste. Not exactly a ringing endorsement for foods
that are full of fiber and virtually fat-free. But in recent years,
chefs have developed recipes for greens that make cooking the
leaves faster and eating them, well easier. BY RUTH FANTASIA.
</P>
<P>
   SPORTS (`s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   FBN-RATTO (San Francisco) _ The latest development in the San
Francisco 49ers' angst-o-rama came when Bill Walsh publicly snarled
at the platoon of amateur jewelers measuring his wrist for a
retirement watch.
</P>
<P>
   He covered everything from ignorance to lack of respect to age
discrimination, and came very close to just dropping a blanket
``Shut your cakeholes!'' on the assembled. By RAY RATTO.
</P>
