   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MORSE-COLUMN (San Francisco) _ It had to happen, but it happened
awfully soon. I heard the phrase ``You're too 20th century.'' The
20th century _ that was so 13 days ago. The nasty comment wasn't
directed at me, but it might as well have been. A lot of us are not
now and never have been dot-commies. By ROB MORSE.
</P>
<P>
   SALTER-COLUMN (San Francisco) _ We kicked it off at 8 p.m., with
an unidentified chorus singing, ``In the Good Old Summertime,'' and
we ended it seven hours and 40 minutes later with REM's ``Losing My
Religion.'' This was a marathon music fest that anchored the New
Year's Eve party I attended featuring the music from every decade
of the 20th century. By STEPHANIE SALTER.
</P>
<P>
   LYNCH-COLUMN (Albany, N.Y.) _ As I ponder the prospect of Sol
Greenberg, the Albany County district attorney, investigating and
prosecuting official corruption, I believe the politicians could be
selling off the state Capitol building, block by block, and Sol
would be the very last guy to notice. By DAN LYNCH.
</P>
<P>
   SERBIA-CHECHNYA (Carmel, Calif.) _ There are many similarities
between the wars in Serbia and Chechnya, both in concept and in
execution. Russia has learned from our example. NATO bombed Serbia
into submission. Russia hopes to bomb Chechnya into submission. By
ALEX A. VARDAMIS.
</P>
