a Canadian woman arrested at a remote Vermont border crossing last
month telephoned associates of an Algerian man arrested in
Washington state days earlier. They also for the first time drew
links between Lucia Garofalo and a man arrested in New York last
month on charges that he was involved in a possible bomb plot in
the Seattle area. (Summary from wires.) By John Kifner.
