one man says Gore will never be elected unless he distances himself
from President Clinton. ``I never would have done that with Monica
Lewinsky,'' Gore said in response. By CRAGG HINES.
</P>
<P>
   GOP-OLD-SOUTH (Undated) _ The ghost of the Old South is haunting
the top two Republican candidates who will have what could be their
final face-off in South Carolina's primary on Feb. 19. Sen. John
McCain of Arizona has praised the state's flag, which now contains
the Confederate symbol, as a sign of Southern heritage. Texas Gov.
George W. Bush, meanwhile, is under fire for campaigning at a
plantation where slaves were bought and sold. By CLAY ROBISON and
BENNETT ROTH.
</P>
