A4122 &Cx1f; tad-z
r e BC-VIDEO-MINIS13-COX     01-12 0268
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-VIDEO-MINIS13-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Mini movie reviews
 &HT;    By Steve Murray and Eleanor Ringel Gillespie
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Lake Placid'' (R) _ In this sometimes watchable,
underpopulated ``Jaws'' retread about a giant crocodile, the croc
attacks are predictable and rudimentary. This is the sort of movie
in which no one but bit players get their heads bitten off. Pity.
The scares aren't scary, the laughs aren't funny, and poor Bridget
Fonda has to keep falling off moving vehicles (boats, trucks)
directly into the path of the monster croc, like some 1940s hapless
heroine. Grade: C-
</P>
<P>
   _ Steve Murray
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Relax ... It's Just Sex'' (unrated) _ Mitchell Anderson,
Jennifer Tilly and Lori Petty star in this big ensemble
comedy-drama about a group of gay and straight friends in Los
Angeles, falling in and out of love. The repartee and observations
are often sharp and witty, but midway through the movie loses its
focus. Grade: B-
</P>
<P>
   _Steve Murray
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Detroit Rock City'' (R) _ Kiss it off. This lame rip-off of
Robert Zemeckis' ``I Wanna Hold Your Hand'' chronicles the
misadventures of four die-hard Kiss fans as they try to crash their
idols' concert. Set in 1978, the film has a few amusing nostalgic
touches, but mostly it's a sorry collection of adolescent fantasies
that look almost quaint compared to what else went on in teen
movies last summer. Grade: D+
</P>
<P>
   _Eleanor Ringel Gillespie
</P>
<P>
   Steve Murray and Eleanor Ringel Gillespie writes for the Atlanta
Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
