<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 GUIDE13-COX &HT;    We've located hard to find items
 &HT;    By Marylin Johnson
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Having trouble finding a particular item? We'll try to help you
locate it. But due to the volume of mail, we cannot track down
every request. Readers whose queries are answered in the column
will receive a blue-and-cream canvas Buyer's Edge tote bag. Write
us at Buyer's Edge Find It, Atlanta Journal-Constitution, P.O. Box
4689, Atlanta, GA 30302; e-mail us at buyersedge(at)ajc.com (please
include your name, the city you live in and daytime phone number);
or call 404-582-7642.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Can you tell me where to order Flutie Flakes? It's a cereal
from Buffalo Bills quarterback Doug Flutie. A portion of the money
raised from the sale of the cereal benefits autistic children.
</P>
<P>
   _ Charles Mejeris, Riverdale, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   A: We can pass on the following information to you. Buy the
20-ounce box of frosted cornflakes ($4.95) in a red or blue box at
www.plbsports.com. Click on football products/Flutie Flakes/product
orders/product listing. Or you can call 1-800-897-1127.Quarterback
Flutie gives a percentage of the sales to the Doug Flutie Jr.
Foundation to Fight Autism.
</P>
<P>
   Q: We moved here 10 years ago and discovered pepper bacon. At
that time I bought it at Cub Foods but have not been able to find
it for the last two to three years. Do you think you could locate
it for me? My husband really enjoyed it.
</P>
<P>
   _ Carol Conlin, Stone Mountain, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   A: You can bring home the bacon once again. We found tasty
Hamtastic Peppered Bacon at Harry's Farmers Market, 2025 Satellite
Pointe, Duluth (770-416-6900). Distributed by Harper's Country Hams
in Clinton, Ky., it's cured with salt, sugar and pepper, which you
can see on each slice. A 12-ounce package is $3.69.
</P>
<P>
   It's also available at $2.69 for a 12-ounce package at Echol's
Jaemor Farm Market on Ga. 365 in Alto (770-869-0999). This
year-round market also features gifts and pottery as well as
home-grown vegetables and fruits.
</P>
<P>
   Q: So far, I'm having lousy luck trying to find the Joel
Williams Thin-Profile Wallet. Originally, it was available on the
Internet at www.fieldtrips.com, but a salesman told me they no
longer carry this wallet, which, according to manufacturer
information, conforms to your body's contours. Can you help?
</P>
<P>
   _ Zachary Willat, Pacific Grove, Calif.
</P>
<P>
   A: This wallet just may be good for your health. Jerry Enebo,
owner of McDandee, which manufactures the Joel Williams wallet,
once worked in the same building with the inventor of the wallet.
``I told the man my back hurt,'' said Enebo. ``He in turn asked to
see my wallet, a bulky, overstuffed trifold that I carried in my
back pocket. Immediately, he gave me one of his wallets, and after
carrying this awhile, my back problems stopped. Now I give them as
gifts to friends who sit or stand for long periods of time with a
conventional billfold in their back pocket.''
</P>
<P>
   The Thin-Profile Wallet contains four pockets for cards. A
second crease allows the leather to conform to your body. To carry
the wallet, wear the zippered pocket toward your body for proper
contouring. Each wallet is $49. To order, call 1-888-925-5388. Or
order on the Internet at home.att.net/(tilde)mcdandee.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I used to be able to find my favorite California Pizza
Kitchen frozen pizza, Rosemary Chicken Potato, at most grocery
stores. Now I can't find it anywhere. Every store seems to sell the
other varieties, but not this one.
</P>
<P>
   _ Beth Welch, Atlanta
</P>
<P>
   A: This yummy-sounding pizza is hard to find, but we managed to
unearth it at Publix, 1265 Pleasant Hill Road, Duluth, Ga.
(770-806-2780). A 12.93-ounce pie is $4.99. The crust is topped
with bordelaise butter sauce, garlic white chicken, mozzarella
cheese, roasted rosemary potatoes and oregano.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I recently moved to Atlanta and haven't been able to find
Mapo Bath Oil Concentrate. Any suggestions?
</P>
<P>
   _ Smiti Kumar,
</P>
<P>
   Atlanta
</P>
<P>
   A: You can now get rid of ``crocodile'' skin with Mapo Bath Oil,
distributed by Merz Skin Care Products in Greensboro, N.C.
Unfortunately, the oil, which according to the label,``softens,
smooths and soothes dry, flaky, itchy skin,'' is not widely
distributed. However, you can order it at 1-800-334-0514. An
8-ounce bottle is $5.88, including shipping; a 16-ounce bottle is
$10.08 including shipping.
</P>
<P>
   _Contributing: Michelle C. Brooks
</P>
