</P>
<P>
   AOL-OPTIONS _ Turner employees, like those of AOL, have for
years been paid in stock. When Time Warner bought Turner, they
jumped for joy because the stock finally became worth something.
Since Monday, it has become worth even more. Also, those with
options (we think) will immediately be able to exercise them. A
change in control of the company automatically vests those options.
We're trying to find out if Turner employees are suddenly much
richer. (Haddad, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
