roof, oh-so-fashionable bird's-eye maple wood trim and a hefty
chrome Jaguar hood ornament, is priced at $42,500 and up.
</P>
<P>
   More sporty, but equally impressive is the two-seater Mercedes
Kompressor, available in a coppery metallic exterior with orange
accents in the black leather upholstery and the center panel. The
little roadster also sports oval exhaust pipes instead of the usual
round design.
</P>
<P>
   Also to be considered is the Volvo C70 convertible, presented
with a metallic cinnamon exterior and champagne leather interior
with red walnut trim and elegantly appointed vanity mirrors. Note:
Illuminated vanity mirrors are still not considered standard
equipment.
</P>
<P>
   DISCOUNT DIVA
</P>
<P>
   Style really matters, but frankly she can't afford those luxe
labels. She buys her clothes at off-price stores, and when it comes
to cars, she's equally savvy.
</P>
<P>
   For her, Chevrolet's Monte Carlo LS Coupe is at its best in
black with ebony animal-print cloth interior, priced at $21,296.
It's got nice vanity mirrors and lots of conveniences, but the
curvy silhouette and futuristic taillights encased in clear plastic
make the style statement. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   CITIFIED COWGIRL
</P>
<P>
   Hauling hay, antique furniture, golden retrievers and more.
Something that kicks up the dust on the back roads and makes her
feel like she's heading to a ranch in Texas instead of the studio
lot in Burbank. We're talking trucks, and the GMC 4X4 Sierra is the
hottest ticket.
</P>
<P>
   This classic pickup truck comes in creamy fire-engine red with a
passenger cab (three doors), sports gray leather upholstery, a
snack table, really deep wells in the drink holders, and oh yeah,
it's got an overhead console to hold sunglasses, garage door
openers and maps. The final touch is some vintage-inspired chrome
trim on the sides of the cab and the bumpers, and a lowered step
that makes the cab easy to hop into. The bottom line? $33,000.
</P>
<P>
   For $10,000 less, the Ford four-door pickup (also in creamy
red), is loaded with style, right down to its chrome-trimmed wheels
and fenders and the ``step-up'' for women drivers. Waxing
nostalgic, Ford installed a bench seat instead of buckets and used
gray vinyl and fabric upholstery, which is great for lovers
watching the sun come up. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
