E. Allen compiled the photos in ``Without Sanctuary: Lynching
Photography in America.'' The book chronicles American lynchings
that took place between 1883 and 1960, mostly but not always in the
South. Most of the images were taken by professional photographers
immediately or a short while after the lynching, sometimes during.
All but a few of the victims were African-American men and women.
(Fred R. Conrad/The New York Times)
