 _ SF CHRON  
 OTHER PC-TO-PHONE SERVICES  &HT;     By David A. Steinberg 
 &HT;     c.2000 San Francisco Chronicle  
<TEXT>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL; 
 &LR; Dialpad is the only completely free service, but other companies
offer promotional or discounted PC-to-phone service, and several
also have discounted phone-to-phone dialing plans. Some sites can't
be accessed through firewalls.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
_Callrewards (www.callrewards.com): You get 20 minutes free for
signing up and have to earn additional minutes by referring friends
or ``interacting'' with advertising offers. Initially, the service
is offering calls only to U.S. phone numbers but plans to start
international service soon.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
DeltaThree (www.deltathree.com): Paid plan. Sample rates: 3.9
cents/minute to the United States and Canada; 8 cents/minute to
Britain; 19 cents/minute to Mexico (25 cents/minute to Mexico
City); 11 cents/minute to Japan (10 cents/ minute to Tokyo).
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
_MediaRing.com (www.mediaring.com): A free promotional plan, in
which you can make unlimited 25-minute calls to U.S. phones, is
expected to last ``for several months.'' Otherwise, this is a paid
plan. Sample rates: 10 cents/minute to the United States and
Canada; 10 cents/minute to Britain; 25 cents/minute to Mexico; 17
cents/minute to Japan (16 cents/minute to Tokyo). Getting to the
free calling area is somewhat difficult: You can't use the default
dialer to access the free calls; instead, you have to go back to
the free promo page for each call. Quality is pretty good, though.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
_Net.Caller (www.accesspower.com): Unlimited calls to the United
States and Canada for $10 per month. Unlimited calls to 12 European
countries plus the United States, Canada and Puerto Rico for $20
per month.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
Net2Phone (www.net2phone.com): One of the first Web sites to offer
PC-to-phone service. Paid plan. Sample rates: 3.9 cents/minute to
the United States and Canada; 4.9 cents/minute to Britain
(3.9/minute to London); 12 cents/minute to Mexico (7 cents/minute
to Mexico City and 25 cents/minute to cell phones); 6 cents/minute
to Japan (5 cents/ minute to Tokyo).
</P>
