 &QL; 
 &UR; SCANNERS _ &LR;  Until recently, even the most wired of mobile warriors
had to resort to pen, paper or copy machine if she came across a
useful article or image at a client's office or in the library.
Even if with a laptop, scanning the item in wasn't an option,
because most scanners were simply too bulky to take on the road.
</P>
<P>
   Today, however, that's changing: Some new models are small and
light enough for a briefcase, a purse or in some cases even a
pocket. Of course, these new mobile scanners are still far from
matching the capabilities of their desktop cousins, but little by
little, they're making scanning on the go a realistic possibility.
By Henry Norr
</P>
